<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-12T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="1766" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1766">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/147.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister to
                            Honduras</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-12T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1912—4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Department learns that revolutionary activities are at present in
                            progress in Guatemala under Generals Prudencio Alfaro and Lino A.
                            Barahona, and that President Bonilla is cooperating with the President
                            of Guatemala. Immediately bring this to the attention of the Government
                            of Honduras and urge strict observance of the Washington
                            conventions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>